  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations in Washington total $12.1B in FY2026 to date, with 71,223 awards and an average award size of $170K. Obligations are down 23.4% year over year. Historical annual obligations show fluctuations: FY21 was $15.6B, FY22 was $12.1B, FY23 was $13B, FY24 was $15.4B, FY25 was $15.8B, and FY26 is $12.1B to date. The Department of Defense accounts for the largest share of buying at $8.2B, followed by the Department of Energy at $2.8B. At the vendor level, THE BOEING COMPANY received $5.8B and BATTELLE MEMORIAL INSTITUTE received $1.1B. Major industries include Aircraft Manufacturing at $5.8B and Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $1.1B. The data reflect contract obligations only and represent partial current-year totals for FY2026 to date.",
    "sections": [
