        "heading": "What is the current spending trend in Washington?",
        "body": "Obligations for FY2026 to date are $12.1B, down 23.4% year over year. Annual obligations have varied, with FY25 at $15.8B and FY26 at $12.1B to date, indicating a lower current-year total compared with the most recent full fiscal year."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Where is federal contract spending concentrated?",
        "body": "Spending is concentrated in defense and energy: the Department of Defense obligates $8.2B and the Department of Energy obligates $2.8B in FY2026 to date. Industry concentration mirrors those buyers, with Aircraft Manufacturing at $5.8B and Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences at $1.1B."
      }
